  {
    "Name": "Grounded: Loss at the Salton Sea",
    "Address": "",
    "Category": "Art Installation",
    "Artist Name": "Andee Strickland",
    "Abridged Project Text": "'Grounded: Loss at the Salton Sea' is a site-specific art installation at the Bombay Beach Marina that directly addresses the dramatic water loss and environmental decline of the Salton Sea.\nThe project will feature a boat cut in half widthwise and partially ~ bedded into the dry marina basin, positionea as if wrecked and permanently stranded. \n\nThe work transforms the abandoned marina into a powerful visual statement about disappearance, environmental fragility, and the consequences of water depletion.",
    "Lat": 33.35215968450866,
    "Long": -115.73263
